  "texts": [
    "In the word embedding process, each token is embedded into a high-dimensional vector (or matrix).",
    "If E is the embedding matrix and x is the input token, then the embedding e is given by e Ex =.",
    "This word embedding process provides a way to represent the input text as a sequence of vectors that attempts to capture the semantic meaning and context of each word (they can capture the general semantics and context but can also struggle with nuanced meaning in some cases).",
    "The word embedding of a decoderonly LLM (Radford et al., 2018 (Radford et al.,, 2019;; Brown et al., 2020) is obtained by feeding the input text into an embedding layer, which maps each word to a vector of a fixed dimension (see Figures 1A, B for an illustration of the typical word embedding network in an LLM).",
    "The embedding layer can be randomly initialized or initialized pretrained weights from another model."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
